label.value: chemotaxis within host

definition.value: The directed movement of a motile cell or organism in response to a specific chemical concentration gradient within its host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

label.value: chemotaxis on or near host involved in symbiotic interaction

definition.value: The directed movement of a motile cell or organism in response to a specific chemical concentration gradient on or near its host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

label.value: negative energy taxis in host

definition.value: The directed movement of a motile cell or organism within its host organism towards a lower level of a physical stimulus involved in energy generation, such as light, oxygen, and oxidizable substrates. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

label.value: negative energy taxis on or near host

label.value: cell wall thickening

definition.value: A type of cell wall modification in which the cell wall is reinforced and made thicker.

label.value: malate dehydrogenase (menaquinone) activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction: (S)-malate + a menaquinone = oxaloacetate + a menaquinol.

label.value: carboxylic ester hydrolase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of a carboxylic ester bond.

label.value: tRNA-specific adenosine-34 deaminase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction: adenosine-34 + H2O = inosine-34 + NH3, in a tRNA-Ala molecule.

label.value: periplasmic flagellum

definition.value: Flagellar filaments located in the periplasmic space; characterized in spirochetes, in which they are essential for shape and motility. Composed of a core surrounded by two sheath layers, the flagella rotate to allow migration of the cell through viscous media, which would not be possible using external flagella.

label.value: oxidation-reduction process

definition.value: A metabolic process that results in the removal or addition of one or more electrons to or from a substance, with or without the concomitant removal or addition of a proton or protons.

label.value: collagen and cuticulin-based cuticle extracellular matrix

definition.value: A collagen and cuticulin-based noncellular, multilayered structure that is synthesized by an underlying ectodermal (hypodermal) cell layer. The cuticle serves essential functions in body morphology, locomotion, and environmental protection. An example of this component is found in Caenorhabditis elegans.

label.value: cell pole

definition.value: Either of two different areas at opposite ends of an axis of a cell.
Note that this term differs from 'cell tip ; GO:0051286' in that it is applicable to a broader range of cell shapes.

label.value: cell chemotaxis

definition.value: The directed movement of a motile cell guided by a specific chemical concentration gradient. Movement may be towards a higher concentration (positive chemotaxis) or towards a lower concentration (negative chemotaxis).

label.value: regulation of wound healing

definition.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the series of events that restore integrity to a damaged tissue, following an injury.

label.value: negative regulation of wound healing

definition.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the series of events that restore integrity to a damaged tissue, following an injury.

label.value: peptidase regulator activity

definition.value: Modulates the activity of a peptidase, any enzyme that catalyzes the hydrolysis peptide bonds.

label.value: endopeptidase regulator activity

definition.value: Modulates the activity of a peptidase, any enzyme that hydrolyzes nonterminal peptide bonds in polypeptides.

label.value: cell chemotaxis involved in Malpighian tubule morphogenesis

definition.value: The directed movement of the outgrowing Malpighian tubule guided by specific chemical cues/signals. Movement may be towards a guidance cue (positive chemotaxis) or away from it (negative chemotaxis). Guidance contributes to the final positioning of the tubule.

label.value: colon epithelial cell chemotaxis

definition.value: The directed movement of a colon epithelial cell guided by a specific chemical concentration gradient. Movement may be towards a higher concentration (positive chemotaxis) or towards a lower concentration (negative chemotaxis).

label.value: canonical glycolysis

definition.value: The glycolytic process that begins with the conversion of glucose to glucose-6-phosphate by glucokinase activity. Glycolytic processes are the  chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a carbohydrate into pyruvate, with the concomitant production of a small amount of ATP.
